Madakoe's Logic
Obviously, I can't just grab the answer straight from a later part of the book. What I need to do is take these situations and use the ones in TToAJ as they're first presented to me, to figure out all the possibilities from that and deduct down to the right one. The first thing I need to think about is what would happen if I went in my pod right now? I feel like the obvious answer is that Seretta would jump out and kill me. But how would she do that? She'd have to get out of her pod first, and... I guess the obvious comparison there is Lauren's mask, something you can't take off easily. Can her mask just be pulled off at all? Based on just what we see in that second chapter, there are a few possibilities... * Lauren could easily remove her mask, but nobody else could * Anyone could remove her mask with enough effort, it's just difficult * Her mask is impossible to remove once it's on there, even by herself * Lauren's mask isn't really a mask at all, it's just part of her body
...How would that first possibility even work, actually? The difference between a pod and a mask is that a pod like this is something you have wiggle room in. There could easily be any number of things hidden in there. A button to open it manually, a detector to open it automatically, anything up to a broom. With a mask, it's fully affixed to your face. Your hands aren't in it, so there's no way you could have some sort of advantage as far as removing it goes. I guess there could be a button in the mask you have to like, push with your nose or something? That'd still let someone else just push the mask into your nose and then activate it that way, and it seems like you'd end up accidentally pressing it a lot anyway. (edited)
So it wouldn't work for the mask, but it would for the pod, then? What about the other possibilities? It could just be difficult to remove the glass on this pod, I guess. In this case, removing would be breaking or getting rid of the glass, right? You could count it as pulling away the pod and so removing it from where it's located, but it'd still be "affixed" to the person, or rather you'd still be contained within it. I couldn't really manage either of those, though, but that'd fit with a "difficult" classification; they don't seem to be bolted to the floor or anything.
A mask would always be easy to move around when it's not on someone, but once it's on someone, pure pulling force probably wouldn't work, or at least you'd have to do it with care. Lauren's mask specifically seems like it could conceivably be a kind that would be impossible to remove once it's on someone without destroying it, just out of design. But are these pods like that? I've tried lifting (which is basically pulling) a pod that has someone in it - Seretta's. But that'd presumably be heavier because... she's in it. It's a heavy pod, and then a tiefling in it; me not being able to push it doesn't mean I can't push the pods themselves. So if I want to treat these pods like a mask of the Lauren type, can I lift, or pull, this opened pod, not attached to anyone? (edited)
I walk over to my pod and try to pull it forwards.

So did she run away, try to get out of their grasp with them all knowing? But she's been in here or asleep in her pods the whole time, so why would she have a room to suddenly retreat to?
But then what does that mean? She's never been asleep in her pod? Or.... is that true? I don't think I've ever heard Seretta mention anything that's happened to her in the real world, but when have I done that? If Seretta can suddenly go up to a hidden room and skip pod day, that has to mean she's working with Q, right?

If Seretta's pod was special, though, then she'd have to have hers custom-designed. Not in an instantly noticeable way, but she'd have to be able to both get out and avoid falling asleep and going back to the real world. So is that why the pods are labelled?
